# ResQ-AI — Project Workflow Rundown

## High-Level Architecture

ResQ-AI is an **autonomous disaster-response drone agent** built on NVIDIA Isaac Sim. The project follows a three-phase pipeline:

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["Phase 1<br/>Situational Awareness<br/>(YOLO Detection)"] --> B["Phase 2<br/>Structural Segmentation<br/>(Pixel-level Masks)"]
    B --> C["Phase 3<br/>Autonomous Flight<br/>(Cosmos Reason 2 VLM)"]
```

---

## End-to-End Data Flow

This is the real-time **Sense → Think → Act** loop that runs during a demo flight:

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph SIM["Simulation Layer (sim_bridge/)"]
        S1["generate_urban_scene.py<br/>Build USD city + disasters"] --> S2["spawn_drone.py<br/>Pegasus Iris + 3 cameras + IMU"]
        S2 --> S3["main_sim_loop.py / demo_flight.py<br/>Tick physics, extract frames"]
    end

    subgraph SENSE["Sense (Perception)"]
        S3 -->|RGB frame| Y["YOLO v8<br/>Hazard Detection"]
        S3 -->|Semantic seg| T["thermal_sim.py<br/>Synthetic Thermal IR"]
        S3 -->|Depth map| P["projection_utils.py<br/>2D pixel → 3D world"]
    end

    subgraph THINK["Think (Reasoning)"]
        Y -->|bboxes + class IDs| LG["logic_gates.py<br/>HazardTracker (IoU + debounce)"]
        LG --> OB["orchestrator_bridge.py<br/>OrchestratorBridge.process_frame()"]
        P -->|3D coords| OB
        T -->|thermal frame| OB
        OB -->|Cosmos prompt JSON| VLM["vlm_server.py<br/>Cosmos Reason 2 / NIM / mock"]
    end

    subgraph ACT["Act (Control)"]
        VLM -->|waypoint + reasoning| FSM["demo_flight.py<br/>FlightState machine<br/>SURVEY → INVESTIGATE → RETURN"]
        FSM -->|lerp position| S2
    end

    subgraph OUTPUT["Outputs"]
        FSM --> RPT["Flight_Report.json"]
        RPT --> MAP["generate_map.py<br/>Folium Hazard Map (HTML)"]
        FSM --> VID["Annotated MP4 video"]
    end
```

---

## Module-by-Module Breakdown

### 1. Scene Generation — [generate_urban_scene.py](file:///c:/Users/anshu/College/CosmosCookoff/ResQ-AI/sim_bridge/generate_urban_scene.py)

| What it does | Details |
|---|---|
| Writes a [.usda](file:///c:/Users/anshu/College/CosmosCookoff/ResQ-AI/resqai_preview.usda) file with a procedural city | Grid of city blocks, roads, sidewalks, parks |
| Places Brownstone assets | CityEngine buildings from `assets/Architecture/` |
| Vegetation & props | Trees, shrubs, benches, hydrants, dumpsters |
| Civilians | Reallusion character references placed on sidewalks |
| **Disaster zones** | Fire (omni.flow) + smoke, collapsed rubble piles |
| Drone ops | Spawn point Xform + camera waypoint markers |
| Semantic labels | Every prim class-labeled for segmentation camera |

**Key config**: `BLOCK_W`, `ROAD_W`, `NUM_COLS/ROWS`, asset centering offsets. All CityEngine assets are in cm so they need `scale=0.01`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> There is also a **root-level** [orchestrator.py](file:///c:/Users/anshu/College/CosmosCookoff/ResQ-AI/orchestrator.py) (1745 lines) that is an older, monolithic standalone version. It builds the scene + runs the sim + does detection all in one file. The **modular** approach in `sim_bridge/` + `orchestrator/` is the current direction.

---

### 2. Drone Spawning — [spawn_drone.py](file:///c:/Users/anshu/College/CosmosCookoff/ResQ-AI/sim_bridge/spawn_drone.py)

Spawns a **Pegasus Iris multirotor** with three Replicator camera sensors mounted at 45° downward pitch:

| Sensor | Class | Resolution | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| RGB | `ReplicatorCamera` | 640×480 @ 30Hz | YOLO hazard detection |
| Semantic Seg | `SemanticSegmentationCamera` | 640×480 | Per-pixel class IDs → thermal |
| Depth | `DepthCamera` | 640×480 | 2D→3D projection |

Also attaches an `IMUStreamBackend` for accelerometer / gyroscope / orientation (body FRD frame) — intended for RL flight stabilization.

---

### 3. Simulation Loop — [main_sim_loop.py](file:///c:/Users/anshu/College/CosmosCookoff/ResQ-AI/sim_bridge/main_sim_loop.py) / [demo_flight.py](file:///c:/Users/anshu/College/CosmosCookoff/ResQ-AI/sim_bridge/demo_flight.py)

Two variants exist:

| Script | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `main_sim_loop.py` | Generic loop: loads scene, spawns drone, ticks physics, calls `OrchestratorBridge.process_frame()` each tick |
| `demo_flight.py` | **Full demo**: adds a `FlightState` machine (`SURVEY → INVESTIGATE → RETURN`), records annotated video, writes `Flight_Report.json` |

**`demo_flight.py` FlightState machine:**
1. **SURVEY** — fly to an observation altitude (45m), run YOLO + thermal + depth
2. **INVESTIGATE** — VLM returns a waypoint; drone lerps toward it, hovers 3s for analysis
3. **RETURN** — after `MAX_INVESTIGATIONS` (5), return to base

Each frame extracts RGB/depth/semantic via `_extract_*()` helpers, feeds them to the `OrchestratorBridge`.

---

### 4. Perception Pipeline

#### 4a. YOLO Detection (Phase 1)
- **Model**: YOLOv8-Small, trained on AIDER dataset
- **Classes**: `Collapsed Building`, `Fire`, `Flood`, `Traffic Incident`
- **Weights**: [best.pt](file:///c:/Users/anshu/College/CosmosCookoff/ResQ-AI/Phase1_SituationalAwareness/best.pt) / `best.onnx` / `best.engine` (TensorRT)
- Loaded by `OrchestratorBridge.__init__()` from `orchestrator_bridge.py`

#### 4b. 2D → 3D Projection — [projection_utils.py](file:///c:/Users/anshu/College/CosmosCookoff/ResQ-AI/sim_bridge/projection_utils.py)
- `pixel_to_3d_world()`: pinhole inverse-projection using depth map + camera intrinsics + camera-to-world transform
- `batch_pixel_to_3d_world()`: one call for all YOLO bbox centers
- `make_intrinsics_from_fov()`: builds K matrix matching Pegasus MonocularCamera defaults

#### 4c. Synthetic Thermal — [thermal_sim.py](file:///c:/Users/anshu/College/CosmosCookoff/ResQ-AI/sim_bridge/thermal_sim.py)
- Converts semantic segmentation class IDs → grayscale thermal-IR image
- Uses a lookup table: `fire` → hottest (255), `person` → warm, `vegetation` → cool, etc.
- Adds Gaussian noise for realism

---

### 5. Decision & Reasoning Pipeline (`orchestrator/`)

#### 5a. Hazard Tracking — [logic_gates.py](file:///c:/Users/anshu/College/CosmosCookoff/ResQ-AI/orchestrator/logic_gates.py)
- `HazardTracker`: temporal debounce + spatial IoU filtering
- A detection must persist ≥ `debounce_frames` (5) consecutive frames before becoming "active"
- Prevents false-positive flicker

#### 5b. Orchestrator Bridge — [orchestrator_bridge.py](file:///c:/Users/anshu/College/CosmosCookoff/ResQ-AI/orchestrator/orchestrator_bridge.py)
- `OrchestratorBridge.process_frame()` is the **central hub**:
  1. Run YOLO on RGB frame
  2. Feed boxes to `HazardTracker`
  3. Project active hazard centers to 3D via `batch_pixel_to_3d_world()`
  4. Build a Cosmos Reason 2 JSON prompt with `build_cosmos_prompt()`
  5. Async-send crop + prompt to VLM server via `_query_vlm_async()`
  6. Return frame results (boxes, labels, 3D coords, waypoint if available)

#### 5c. VLM Server — [vlm_server.py](file:///c:/Users/anshu/College/CosmosCookoff/ResQ-AI/orchestrator/vlm_server.py)
FastAPI server with three backends:

| Backend | Flag | Description |
|---|---|---|
| **Mock** | `--backend mock` | Deterministic priority-based waypoint (no GPU) |
| **NIM Cloud** | `--backend nim` | NVIDIA NIM API (needs `NVIDIA_API_KEY`) |
| **vLLM Local** | `--backend vllm` | Self-hosted Cosmos Reason 2 via vLLM |

Endpoint: `POST /analyze` — accepts `{image_base64, context}`, returns waypoint + reasoning JSON.

---

### 6. Outputs

#### Flight Report
`demo_flight.py` writes `Flight_Report.json` containing each detected hazard with:
- Class name, hazard ID, frame index
- 3D world coordinates
- VLM analysis text
- Image crop path

#### Hazard Map — [generate_map.py](file:///c:/Users/anshu/College/CosmosCookoff/ResQ-AI/orchestrator/generate_map.py)
- Reads `Flight_Report.json`
- Converts sim world XYZ → approximate lat/lon
- Generates interactive **Folium** HTML map with clickable markers (image popups + VLM analysis)

---

## Phase Status & Integration Points

| Phase | Status | Key Integration Point |
|---|---|---|
| **Phase 1** (YOLO Detection) | ✅ Complete | Weights loaded by `OrchestratorBridge` |
| **Phase 2** (Segmentation) | 🚧 In Progress | Colab notebooks ready; needs training → export → plug into pipeline alongside YOLO |
| **Phase 3** (Cosmos Reasoning) | 🔧 Setup Done | `setup_cosmos.py` loads model; `vlm_server.py` wraps it; `orchestrator_bridge.py` sends prompts |

---

## How to Run the Full Demo

```bash
# 1. Start the VLM server (in a separate terminal)
cd orchestrator
python vlm_server.py --backend mock   # or --backend nim / --backend vllm

# 2. Run the full demo flight (requires Isaac Sim 5.1)
cd sim_bridge
python demo_flight.py --vlm-url http://localhost:8000/analyze

# 3. Generate the hazard map from the flight report
cd orchestrator
python generate_map.py --report ../Flight_Report.json
```

